048d">N05 (VI.B.2):048(d)</a> When English peasants and artsians rebelled against feudalism in 1381, their slogan was the couplet preached by John Ball at Blackheath: &ldquo;When Adam delved, and Eve span, who was then the gentleman?&rdquo; </mm> </dd></dl>
